#
#  Text 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-BME-18-064.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

Show shoulder abduction in the frontal plane with a weight in the hand is a common exercise to strengthen the deltoids. If [`F_1 = [$f1]`] and [`F_2 = [$f2]`], what is the force ([`F_M`]) required in the left deltoid to sustain a weight held in the hand at an abduction angle of [`90^{\circ}`]? Assume that [`F_1`] and [`F_2`] are [`[$d1]`] [`cm`] and [`[$d2]`] [`cm`] away from the center of the scapulo-humeral joint, respectively, and assume that the deltoid acts alone at an angle of [`[$theta]^{\circ}`] above the horizontal with a moment arm of [`[$d]`] [`cm`].

[`F_M=`] [_____]{"$fm"} [`N`]  

END_PGML

